The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	 Mohun Bagan are in a spot of bother regarding their home matches in the AFC Cup. The Asian Football Confederation has stated that the money received from hoarding and billboards while hosting a match will be deposited into the confederations account. Bagan officials fear that they would incur a hefty loss due to the decision.      
	We need to plan our next move in an executive committee meeting in the next seven to 10 days and thereafter, shall convey our stand to the AFC, club general secretary Anjan Mitra said on Tuesday.      
	Bagan, meanwhile, will play a warm-up match against Budge Budge Academy on Wednesday as a part of their preparation for the second phase of the I-League.           
	 East Bengal beat Customs 2-0 in a practice match at the club grounds on Tuesday. Parveen Kumar and Mehtab Hossain scored for East Bengal. It was the clubs first match under new coach Subhas Bhowmick and drew quite a few supporters.                
	 La Martiniere for Boys beat Lakshmipat Singhania Academy by 87 runs in the Inter-School Twenty20 Championship at the Mainland Sambaran Cricket Academy.       
	SUMMARISED SCORES      
	La Martiniere for Boys 212/3 (R. Lakshmani 104). Lakshmipat Singhania Academy 125/5 (S. Dalmiya 73). La Martiniere won by 87 runs.      
	 National High School for Boys 186/9 (K. Chatterjee 71). Assembly of God Church 131/9 (A. Singh 30). NHS won by 55 runs.                
	 State sports minister Subhas Chakraborty on Tuesday paid a visit to CAB president Jagmohan Dalmiya for about 15 minutes. Asked about the reason behind the surprise visit, the minister said: It was just a courtesy visit.          
